<br>
Captain Linarius rushed up to the guard post as soon as he could see the bodies. He drew his fine steels sword and gripped it tightly, glad the leather-wrapped hilt absorbed the fear sweat upon his palms. Guards Oystin and Shilster had been slaughtered. Their bodies left where they had fell in obvious torment. He knew giants as well as hippogriffs were bad about the area but this this butchery had the look of something more sinister.<br>
<br>
His stomach clenched as he looked up to see what had been plastered on the wall of the guard tower. &quot;Marr preserve us.&quot; The Captain turned and ran from the tower, not looking back. He had to report this to the paladins, to the guards, to anybody who would listen. This was bad, and spelled the potential doom for all of the Lightbringers of Norrath.<br>
<br>
The Ebon Storm was recruiting....<br>
<br>
In the hollowed halls of Felwithe, the high elf leaders sat glumly around their oaken table, wine untouched beside them for the dryness in their throats. Wood elf allies nervously glanced at each other until one of them boldly spoke forth &quot;But what does it mean? Why does this poster cause you so much fear? I've heard they've gone up everywhere.&quot;<br>
<br>
Farios Elianos spoke first. &quot;The Ebon Storm is a blight upon all that is good in the world. They have raided our cities and the tombs of many creatures. Their castle is unassailable and even the planes of the gods have felt the thunder of the Storm. Druids, rangers, and paladins are banned from their ranks as are all of the dal not touched by darkness.&quot;<br>
<br>
The youngest of the wood elves snorted. &quot;Surely they cannot be so dangerous. I mean...just one guild....&quot; His words died as the grim expressions of the high elf guild masters turned toward him.<br>
<br>
&quot;You were the one who took down the poster?&quot; It was Niola of the mage's guild who asked the question.<br>
<br>
He stuck out his chest proudly, the young ranger bold in his pride. &quot;I did. No stupid curse on paper frightens me. I spit on this Ebon Storm.&quot; The wood elf pounded his chest and his eyes sparked in rage, his face beginning to twist in odd contortions of fury &quot;In fact I promise I'll hunt down every one of them! I'll slay them all. I'll...I'll KILL THEM. YES, I'LL KILL THEM ALL!&quot; The last words were near shouted as his eyes glazed over. The young ranger drew his swords and lunged at the assembled elves, slashing the cheek of one elder before the combined magics of the assembled masters reduced the crazed elf to ashes.<br>
<br>
As the smoke cleared, Niola sighed. &quot;Leave the poster where it is. We will find some prisoner to return it to where it was found before the curse takes any other.&quot; With heads bowed and a solemn gait they filed out of the room, doing their best not to glance too long at the dreaded poster....<br>
